.TH JOURNALCTL-ALL 1 "2026-06-07" "journald-archive 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
journalctl-all \- query the combined live + archived systemd journal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B journalctl-all
.RI [ journalctl-options "...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B journalctl-all
is a thin wrapper around
.BR journalctl (1)
that queries the read-only mergerfs union of the hot tier
.RI ( /var/log/journal )
and the compressed archive
.RI ( /var/log/journal_archive ),
exposed at
.IR /var/log/journal_combined .
.PP
It is equivalent to running:
.PP
.RS
.B journalctl --directory=/var/log/journal_combined
.RI [ options "...]"
.RE
.PP
All arguments are passed through to
.BR journalctl (1)
unchanged, so every option behaves identically \(em the only difference is
that the query spans the full retained history (live plus archive) instead of
only the recent logs in the hot tier.
.PP
If the combined view is not currently mounted,
.B journalctl-all
prints a warning naming the mount unit to start, then runs
.BR journalctl (1)
anyway.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B journalctl-all -u nginx --since 2025-01-01
Show all nginx logs since the start of 2025, including archived ones.
.TP
.B journalctl-all --disk-usage
Report the on-disk size across both tiers.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR journalctl (1),
.BR journald-archive (8)
